WE HIT OUR FIRST BUG:

=====================================================================================
I left password and confirm password section blank. It said registration successful

Excellent catch! 👏

This is exactly the kind of testing a good developer (or product builder) does. You found a bug in the code I provided.

Why it happened

In the code, I added validation for:

✅ Full Name
✅ Email
✅ Mobile Number

But I forgot to add validators for:

❌ Password
❌ Confirm Password

So when both fields are empty:

passwordController.text == confirmPasswordController.text

both are empty strings (""), so they are considered equal, and the app incorrectly shows:

Registration Successful (UI Only)

Fix 1: Password Field

Replace your password field with this:

TextFormField(
  controller: passwordController,
  obscureText: hidePassword,
  decoration: InputDecoration(
    labelText: "Password",
    border: const OutlineInputBorder(),
    suffixIcon: IconButton(
      icon: Icon(
        hidePassword ? Icons.visibility : Icons.visibility_off,
      ),
      onPressed: () {
        setState(() {
          hidePassword = !hidePassword;
        });
      },
    ),
  ),
  validator: (value) {
    if (value == null || value.isEmpty) {
      return "Enter password";
    }

    if (value.length < 8) {
      return "Password must be at least 8 characters";
    }

    return null;
  },
),
Fix 2: Confirm Password Field

Replace it with:

TextFormField(
  controller: confirmPasswordController,
  obscureText: hideConfirmPassword,
  decoration: InputDecoration(
    labelText: "Confirm Password",
    border: const OutlineInputBorder(),
    suffixIcon: IconButton(
      icon: Icon(
        hideConfirmPassword
            ? Icons.visibility
            : Icons.visibility_off,
      ),
      onPressed: () {
        setState(() {
          hideConfirmPassword = !hideConfirmPassword;
        });
      },
    ),
  ),
  validator: (value) {
    if (value == null || value.isEmpty) {
      return "Confirm your password";
    }

    return null;
  },
),
